heading: Ghoa Ruins Dungeon Guide
content: Ghoa Ruins has a compact, convoluted layout and hosts dangerous Naragi (Snakes) that use attacks. It is solid for farming, but is not currently a possible . Drowned Seahag is an easy meat piñata boss with only a couple of annoying knockback and attacks. This dungeon unlocks the , a near useless defensive aspect for the Rogue (the Rogue rarely stands still!) While every dungeon has a somewhat randomized layout, there are patterns to where objectives and bosses are located. This map will help you identify those layouts so you can complete dungeons faster and maximize your XP and loot per hour! Reviewed by
